variableFilters.description:
Condition filters on process variables. All conditions must be met for a process instance to be returned (alongside optional ones set on process data, see above).<br><br>You can write each filter following two formalisms:<ul><li>simple: `variable_id: value` (with `value` being a boolean, a number or a text)<ul><li>`filterType` will be an `equals` by default.</li><li>the `value` can be either a boolean, a number or a text.</li></ul></li><li>detailed: `variable_id: {"filterType": "filterType", "value/valueMin": value1, "valueMax": value2}`<ul><li>`filterType` is one of possible values among those described below.</li><li>`value` can be either a `Boolean`, a `Number` or a `Text`. Required for `equals`, `not_equals`, `contains` and `not_contains` filterTypes.</li><li>`valueMin` and `valueMax` need to be a number. Required for `between` and `not_between` filterTypes.</li></ul></li></ul>A filter can be of different types. Here are all the possible values for `filterType`: <ul><li>`empty`: check column is empty (`""`), null, or not initialised.</li><li>`not_empty`: check column is not empty and not null.</li><li>`equals`: check column value is equal to given `value`.</li><li>`not_equals`: check column value is not equal to given `value`.</li><li>`contains`: check column of type value `Text` contains given `value`.</li><li>`not_contains`: check column of type value `Text` does not contains given `value`.</li><li>`between`: check column value of type value `Number` or `Timestamp` (in millisecond) is strictly between given `valueMin` and `valueMax`.</li><li>`not_between`: check column value of type value `Number` or `Timestamp` (in millisecond) is strictly outside given `valueMin` and `valueMax`.</li></ul><b>Warning</b>: you cannot filter twice on the same variableId inside the `variableFilters` object. Ex: following `filterVariables` filter will only apply a "not_equals":<br>
```
{
	"myIntegerId1": {
		"filterType": "between",
		"valueMin": 0,
		"valueMax": 10
	},
	"myIntegerId1": {
		"filterType": "not_equals",
		"value": 6
	}
}
```
